,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/509/tVIII/s8031/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–509, title VIII, § 8031(a)","children":[],"tail":", (b), and (d)(1), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/1955"},"text":"100 Stat. 1955","children":[],"tail":", to subsecs. (a) to (e) of this section were not executed to text pursuant to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/509/tVIII/s8031/e/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–509, title VIII, § 8031(e)(2)","children":[],"tail":", which provided that the amendments made by section 8031 shall not take effect if the Superfund Amendments and Reauthorization Act of 1986 is enacted. The Superfund Amendments and Reauthorization Act of 1986 was enacted as "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/499"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–499","children":[],"tail":", approved "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-10-17"},"text":"Oct. 17, 1986","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id45dd11fb-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2022—Subsec. (c)(2)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/169/s13601/a/2/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–169, § 13601(a)(2)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “16.4 cents” for “9.7 cents”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/169/s13601/a/2/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–169, § 13601(a)(2)(B)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (3)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/169/s13601/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–169, § 13601(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", struck out subsec. (e) which related to application of Hazardous Substance Superfund financing rate."}],"tail":"\n"},{"ta